  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Jane Wigham says that three boxes have been dispatched for the anti-slavery bazaar, and she tells where the contents came from. The exhibition of the contributions had more visitors than any previous one: &quot;hundreds came each of the two days we had them displayed.&quot; This exhibition conflicted with the New Christian Association&apos;s anti-slavery bazaar and was blamed for the latter&apos;s small success. Charles Sumner visited Professor Nichols and his family at the Glasgow Observatory. Jane Wigham describes the numerous items contributed and comments on the contributors.</subfield>
